Timeseries, or well vs

Here I need to graph the time evolution of many experiments, so the idea is to have a graph of coupled vertices counts against .
This will be quite a mess, so I have to get a bit creative on how to display this and for it to be understandable.

The idea behind this graph is to see how different fields and angular velocities behave, and whether or not they reach a steady state.
This one is at 20mT

We can see that there is some value around 0.2 and 0.3 at which the system orders. The counts for Type I+VI simply jump quite rapidly. Is this some sort of transition? I

I still need to make other fields, but I am not sure on what to see for lower fields.

The one above had only the field at 20mT. I did all the fields, and the most important ones were at 5,10 and 20 mT.

Area vs

Here the idea is the following. Get the following area.

Defined as the area under the curve between the curve and the horizontal line gotten from the last point of the curve. the domain is simply the intersection point and the last point in the axis.
This should go to zero as becomes large enough. Or just drop to zero suddenly.

There are some details that I need to explain.

  1. Sometimes there is no point in the data that intersects the horizontal line, and the closest point is very far, giving a negative area between the two curves.
  2. To solve this I made some interpolations to approximate the data curve. It actually works quite well.
  3. And from that compute the integral.

This gives the following graph
